properties.areaDesc: San Diego County Mountains; San Diego County Deserts; Riverside County Mountains; Coachella Valley; San Bernardino County Mountains; San Gorgonio Pass Near Banning; Apple and Lucerne Valleys
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued March 1 at 3:39AM PST until March 2 at 3:00AM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 65 mph expected.
The strongest winds will be on the mountains ridges and down
the eastern mountain slopes into the lower deserts.

* WHERE...San Bernardino County Mountains, Riverside County
Mountains, San Diego County Mountains, Apple and Lucerne
Valleys, Coachella Valley, San Diego County Deserts and San
Gorgonio Pass Near Banning.

* WHEN...Through 3 AM PST Monday, with the strongest winds this
afternoon and tonight.

* IMPACTS...Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages
may result. Visibility may be reduced in blowing dust and sand
at times. High impact areas in the Coachella Valley include Palm
Springs, Palm Desert, La Quinta, I-10 and Highway 111. In the
San Diego County deserts, Borrego Springs, Ocotillo Wells, the
Anza Borrego Desert and I-8 will be affected. In the High
Desert, low visibilities in blowing sand are likely on highways
395, 18, 247 and I- 15.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Peak wind gusts through 3 AM include 54 mph
at Harrison Park and Volcan Mountain in the San Diego County
Mountains. In the High Deserts, Hesperia had a gust to 36 mph.
In the Coachella Valley, Palm Springs and Thermal gusted to 32
mph, and Indio to 30 mph. Borrego Springs had a gust to 25 mph.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM PST MONDAY
